Title : Big Creek Valley, Pennsylvania
Text : '''Big Creek Valley''' was a village in [[Carbon County, Pennsylvania|Carbon County]], [[Pennsylvania]].  In 1966 the village was vacated to make way for Beltzville Lake, located in what is now [[Beltzville State Park]].<ref name="Times News (Pennsylvania) - 04 May 2014 - Big Creek Valley before Beltzville Lake">{{cite news|url=http://www.tnonline.com/2013/may/04/big-creek-valley-beltzville-lake-part-1|title=Big Creek Valley before Beltzville Lake|date=May 4, 2013|work=[[Times News (Pennsylvania)|Times News]]|publisher=Pencor Services, Inc.|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> American composer [[David W. Guion]] may have lived in Big Creek Valley.<ref name="Times News (Pennsylvania) - 11 May 2013 - Home on the Range along Pohopoco Creek">{{cite news|url=http://www.tnonline.com/2013/may/11/home-range-along-pohopoco-creek|title="Home on the Range" along Pohopoco Creek|date=May 11, 2013|work=[[Times News (Pennsylvania)|Times News]]|publisher=Pencor Services, Inc.|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref>

